{"id":37021,"title":"Pathogenesis and prevention of intraventricular hemorrhage.","abstract":"Intraventricular hemorrhage (IVH) is a major neurologic complication of prematurity. Pathogenesis of IVH is attributed to intrinsic fragility of germinal matrix vasculature and to the fluctuation in the cerebral blood flow. Germinal matrix exhibits rapid angiogenesis orchestrating formation of immature vessels. Prenatal glucocorticoid exposure remains the most effective means of preventing IVH. Therapies targeted to enhance the stability of the germinal matrix vasculature and minimize fluctuation in the cerebral blood flow might lead to more effective strategies in preventing IVH. ","date":"2014-02-14","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24524446","annotations":[{"name":"Glucocorticoid","weight":0.889548,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glucocorticoid"},{"name":"Neurology","weight":0.8182,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurology"},{"name":"Angiogenesis","weight":0.775064,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angiogenesis"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.75445,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Pregnancy","weight":0.745082,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pregnancy"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.744909,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Preterm birth","weight":0.735017,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preterm_birth"},{"name":"Blood flow","weight":0.734391,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_flow"},{"name":"Intraventricular hemorrhage","weight":0.720698,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intraventricular_hemorrhage"},{"name":"Circulatory system","weight":0.720049,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circulatory_system"},{"name":"Cerebrum","weight":0.685627,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wi